  "prompt": "Why do I have red itchy balls all over my skin?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry that you're experiencing this. Red itchy bumps can be caused by a variety of factors. Some common causes include:\n\n1. **Allergic Reactions**: You might be allergic to a new soap, lotion, detergent, or fabric.\n2. **Insect Bites**: Bites from insects like mosquitoes or bedbugs can cause red, itchy bumps.\n3. **Heat Rash**: Sweating and hot weather can lead to heat rashes.\n4. **Skin Conditions**: Conditions like eczema, psoriasis, or dermatitis can cause red, itchy patches.\n5. **Infections**: Fungal infections (like ringworm) or bacterial infections can cause itching and redness.\n6. **Hives**: Stress, allergens, or irritants can cause hives, which are red, itchy welts on the skin.\n\nTo avoid worsening the condition, consider:\n\n- **Avoid scratching**: It can irritate the skin further and possibly cause infection.\n- **Keep the area clean**: Gentle washing with mild soap and water can help.\n- **Use soothing lotions**: Products containing calamine or hydrocortisone might provide relief.\n- **Wear loose clothing**: Fabrics that allow your skin to breathe can help prevent further irritation.\n\nIt's important to consult a healthcare professional for an accurate diagnosis and appropriate treatment.",
